gating how postrevolutionary France envisioned the past, Samuels illuminates a vital moment in the cultural history of modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFrench fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aHistory in literature. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aWest European History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172983640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501729836423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501729836/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles